.TH FOLD(1),User Commands,FOLD(1)

.SH NAME
fold - wrap input lines to fit in specified width

.SH SYNOPSIS
fold [-bs] [-w width] [file ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The fold utility wraps each line of the specified files to fit within the specified column width (default 80). If no files are given, standard input is read.

.SH OPTIONS
-b: Count bytes instead of characters. On this platform, bytes and characters are equivalent.

-s: Break lines at the last space character before the width limit, rather than at exactly the width. This avoids splitting words.

-w width: Wrap at width columns (default 80, max 255).

.SH EXIT STATUS
The fold utility exits 0 on success, and >0 if an error occurs.

.SH EXAMPLES
Wrap stdin at 40 columns:

$ fold -w 40

Wrap a file at 72 columns, breaking at spaces:

$ fold -s -w 72 file.txt
